ngland, United Kingdom":"Aldford, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Middlewich, Cheshire, England":"Middlewich, Cheshire, England","Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","Over, Cheshire, England":"Over, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1360–September 1399":"1360–september 1399","1360–1399":"1360–1399","1377–Male":"1377–Overleden","1360–1415":"1360–1415","1380–1435":"1380–1435","1328–1378":"1328–1378","1340–1390":"1340–1390","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1435":"1435","1378":"1378","1377":"1377","1399":"1399","1340":"1340","September 1399":"september 1399","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","Weaver, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Weaver, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Aldford, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Aldford, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Middlewich, Cheshire, England":"Middlewich, Cheshire, England","Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","Over, Cheshire, England":"Over, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1360–September 1399":"1360–September 1399","1360–1399":"1360–1399","1377–Male":"1377–Deceased","1360–1415":"1360–1415","1380–1435":"1380–1435","1328–1378":"1328–1378","1340–1390":"1340–1390","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1435":"1435","1378":"1378","1377":"1377","1399":"1399","1340":"1340","September 1399":"September 1399","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","Weaver, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Weaver, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Aldford, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Aldford, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Middlewich, Cheshire, England":"Middlewich, Cheshire, England","Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","Over, Cheshire, England":"Over, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Weaver","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name, from an agent derivative of Middle English <i>weven</i> ‘to weave’ (Old English <i>wefan</i>).","English: habitational name from a place on the Weaver river in Cheshire, now called Weaver Hall but recorded simply as <i>Weuere</i> in the 13th and 14th centuries. The river name is from Old English <i>wēfer(e)</i> ‘winding stream’.","Americanized form (translation into English) of various European surnames meaning ‘weaver’, for example German   Weber  , Polish and Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic)   Tkacz   or   Tkach  , Hungarian <b>Takács</b> (see   Takacs  ), and Slovenian <b>Tkalec</b>,   Tekavec   or   Veber  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Weber","meanings":["German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): occupational name for a weaver, Middle High German <i>wëber</i>, German <i>Weber</i>, an agent derivative of <i>weben</i> ‘to weave’. This form of the surname is also established in many other parts of Europe, notably in France (mainly Alsace and Lorraine), Poland, and the Netherlands. In Hungary it is mostly spelled <b>Wéber</b> and <b>Véber</b>. In Russia, Slovenia, Czechia, Slovakia, and Croatia it is (also) established in the Slavicized form   Veber  , which is in Czechia also spelled <b>Vebr</b>. Compare   Waber  ,   Weaber  ,   Weaver  ,   Webber  , and   Webre  .","History: As a name of ultimately Swiss German origin the surname <i>Weber</i> is also established among the American Mennonites. However, descendants of the early Mennonite settlers, who came to PA in the early 18th century, mostly bear the Americanized form of the name (see   Weaver  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Weaver was born in 1360, in Weaver, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard de Weaver, was 32 and his mother, Margaret de Arderne, was 20. He had at least 1 son with Isabella de Fulleshurst. He died in September 1399, in his hometown, at the age of 39."},"et":{"1360–September 1399":"1360–september 1399","1360–1399":"1360–1399","1377–Male":"1377–Surnud","1360–1415":"1360–1415","1380–1435":"1380–1435","1328–1378":"1328–1378","1340–1390":"1340–1390","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1435":"1435","1378":"1378","1377":"1377","1399":"1399","1340":"1340","September 1399":"september 1399","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","Weaver, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Weaver, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Aldford, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Aldford, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Middlewich, Cheshire, England":"Middlewich, Cheshire, England","Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","Over, Cheshire, England":"Over, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1360–September 1399":"1360–syyskuu 1399","1360–1399":"1360–1399","1377–Male":"1377–Kuollut","1360–1415":"1360–1415","1380–1435":"1380–1435","1328–1378":"1328–1378","1340–1390":"1340–1390","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1435":"1435","1378":"1378",